verbs.description: misdrive (third-person singular simple present misdrives, present participle misdriving, simple past misdrove, past participle misdriven)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive, rare) To drive badly or wrongly.
examples: Nightly it blazed, and waved its fiery tail,And made the dreaded Ursa Major quail;Destined but once before her fear to prove,When Phaeton the Solar car misdrove.
